          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1620663992479-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped red onion</strong> to the dish with the <strong>sliced carrot</strong>, <strong>crushed garlic </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> beef stock mix</strong> and 450ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[675ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[900ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat – this is your <strong>spicy lamb ragù</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1620663997178-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1620663997178-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1620663997178-x700.jpg",
